cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on using visual cues (face and facial landmarks) for emotion recognition, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper also uses textual cues for emotion recognition, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep neural networks and an ensemble model for emotion recognition, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with emotion recognition from both video and text modalities, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper's focus on automatic emotion recognition has implications for human-computer interaction, as it can be used to improve the emotional intelligence of machines.
